      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COPPER HEAD LADY (3) has had six weeks off since finishing down the track behind a top mare when resuming but has trialled twice in that time. Owns a strong second-up record and is well served by a low draw in what looks a suitable assignment. MY HAMMER DOWN NZ (8) was brave in a first-up win, racing parked before proving too strong by 2.6m. Draws wide but that last win took his record at this circuit and distance to two from three. Fitter and has upside. TAKE A HIKE NZ (7) must be respected after placing in his last five outings at this circuit and distance, the latest from this barrier. OFFICIAL ROCK (5) drew on the back row last start and has claims having come from wider than this to be beaten only a neck as runner-up here two back.",
